# Frontend Experience

- RULE: Design mobile-first and Safari-first.
- RULE: Keep product UI Spanish-first with English as the secondary locale.
- RULE: Keep repository-facing content in English.
- RULE: Favor stable browser APIs and lightweight frontend decisions that work well on WebKit.
- RULE: Treat automated WebKit checks as Safari-adjacent verification, not as a replacement for final manual Safari validation when a slice materially changes mobile layout or interaction.
- RULE: Use Safari Responsive Design Mode and, when needed, Open with Simulator and iOS/iPadOS Web Inspector as the canonical manual validation path for Apple-device layout and interaction issues.
- RULE: Support both light and dark presentation and default to the system color-scheme preference.
- RULE: Target WCAG 2.2 AA in product decisions and avoid public conformance claims until the relevant UI slice is actually audited.
- RULE: Use `Home`, `Planner`, and `Calendario` as the primary public navigation destinations.
- RULE: Keep project/help, AI-connection, inscriptions, configuration, and search surfaces secondary to the primary navigation destinations even when desktop and tablet layouts place them in the same top navigation cluster.
- RULE: Keep executive-education or other less-common official-reference surfaces secondary or overflow-only; they must not become primary navigation destinations.
- RULE: Start the product flow with onboarding inside the planner flow, not behind an account wall.
- RULE: Collect academic level in planner onboarding before deriving entry-term years, planner defaults, or level-specific periods.
- RULE: Collect entry term in onboarding with controlled season/year selectors instead of free-text input.
- RULE: Derive onboarding year-selector options from official published catalog signals for the selected academic level, including bulletin applicability windows and current public periods, instead of exposing arbitrary years.
- RULE: Hide plan selection until the entry-term selectors are complete enough to filter candidate plans.
- RULE: Keep `/` as the public home, `/planner` as the dedicated planner shell, `/planner/onboarding` as the embedded planner-onboarding route, `/calendar` as the public calendar surface, and add secondary public routes for search, project, AI connection, registration guidance, settings, terms, and privacy.
- RULE: Keep public route slugs English-only even when the visible UI is Spanish-first.
- RULE: Keep `/planner` safe even when onboarding is incomplete; browser-side redirects may be used, but the route must still expose a stable fallback path to `/planner/onboarding`.
- RULE: Treat stale browser-local profile state as incomplete when the current published catalog no longer yields an applicable active plan for the stored entry term.
- RULE: Keep the initial planner document lean and fetch heavy schedule detail from precomputed JSON on demand instead of embedding the full catalog detail into the first HTML response.
- RULE: Keep planner onboarding as a guided stepper with explicit back/next progression and a lightweight introductory step.
- RULE: Collect academic level, entry term, a UI-locale step, one or two searchable base-career choices when applicable, optional official joint-program choices when applicable, and default subject selection during planner onboarding.
- RULE: Keep the onboarding locale step valid by default in `es-MX`; users may change it, but the default locale must not require a redundant confirmation click.
- RULE: Support a dedicated `jointPrograms` planner-onboarding mode that skips base-career selection and shows only official joint-program choices for the selected entry term.
- RULE: Sort visible career choices alphabetically and drive their labels from locale configuration rather than leaking raw uppercase catalog labels.
- RULE: Use canonical academic names derived from official ITAM-owned references across onboarding, configuration, search, and planner UI, while keeping stable aliases for matching noisy upstream labels.
- RULE: Deduplicate visible plan rows into searchable academic choices whenever the selected entry term exposes multiple plans for the same official career or joint-program grouping.
- RULE: Seed planner subject selection automatically from the estimated current semester during onboarding, prefer applicable normalized bulletin plans first, and fall back to official ITAM-owned career study-plan references when the current published bulletin catalog lacks an applicable plan for the selected career.
- RULE: Expose official graduate-program and official double-degree references through the public bootstrap/search layer so graduate discovery does not depend on unofficial mirrors.
- RULE: Do not keep already-selected subjects duplicated in the lower available-subject directory.
- RULE: Expose selected public classes explicitly in planner configuration after subject selection so users can keep or remove concrete public groups apart from the subject list.
- RULE: Treat launch planner widget preferences as browser-local UI state, initialize the default launch widget set during planner setup, and keep `Today` visually dominant when present.
- RULE: Keep advanced schedule-generation preferences browser-local and editable from configuration, including teacher-ranking, class clustering, daily time range, lighter-day preference, theory/lab matching, and importance weights.
- RULE: Show swipe-preference controls only on phone layouts, where swipe navigation exists.
- RULE: Recover silently from browser-owned state failures whenever possible and never expose storage-reset internals in routine UI copy.
- RULE: If a visible runtime error state is unavoidable, keep it generic and keep the surrounding route alive.
- RULE: Never wipe browser-local planner state automatically just because a route-level error boundary rendered.
- RULE: Keep an explicit `Under Construction` notice visible while the product is still in scaffold-heavy mode.
- RULE: Treat SEO, crawlability, and structured metadata as product requirements.
- RULE: Drive visible UI strings, route chrome labels, selector labels, ARIA labels, and locale-dependent option labels from locale dictionaries instead of hardcoded component or page strings.
- RULE: Drive public metadata text, structured-data descriptions, and other crawlable locale-facing SEO copy from locale dictionaries instead of hardcoded page-module strings.
- RULE: Drive App Router metadata routes and metadata helpers, including `manifest`, `robots`, `sitemap`, and JSON-LD input copy, from dedicated locale/i18n modules instead of inline literals.
- RULE: Keep frontend identifiers, enum values, configuration keys, and non-locale component APIs English-only; Spanish belongs only in locale dictionaries, source-derived content, and compatibility aliases.
- RULE: Support only `es-MX` and `en` as product locales in the current slice.
- RULE: Any locale-facing text change must update the locale dictionaries and regression tests in the same change.
- RULE: Keep UI modules on the strict path `data -> presenter functions -> locale dictionaries -> UI`.
- RULE: Keep canonical academic program data in one shared source of truth and derive matchers, labels, and fallbacks from that source instead of duplicating them.
- RULE: Keep planner logic, browser persistence, and presentation styling loosely coupled so the visual system can be replaced without rewriting behavior.
- RULE: Keep swipe navigation scoped to the top navigation surface only.
- RULE: Keep swipe interaction and swipe-teaching UI mobile-phone-only; tablet and desktop navigation should use pointer and keyboard interactions instead.
- RULE: Persist the chosen or learned swipe-direction preference browser-locally without changing the semantic destination set.
- RULE: Keep any setup/loading transition browser-local, bounded, and purely cosmetic.
- RULE: Do not instruct users to install the site through browser-native menu entries from within the website UI.
- RULE: Keep a small persistent legal footer with links to Terms and Privacy.
- RULE: Keep workspace launch/task configuration ready for editor-driven browser preview and debugging instead of relying on undocumented local setup.
- RULE: Keep browser-level responsive smoke coverage available across desktop Chromium, phone WebKit, and tablet WebKit profiles for the public web shell.
- RULE: Keep workspace tasks available for terminal, headed, and interactive responsive-smoke debugging instead of requiring ad-hoc local commands.
- RULE: Prefer dynamic viewport units, safe-area environment variables, and resilient fallback sizing for shell-level height and spacing decisions on mobile Safari.
- RULE: Collapse secondary surfaces into a menu trigger whenever the available top-bar width cannot fit the full navigation cluster without wrapping, even on tablet and desktop.
- RULE: Keep the main planner route focused on schedule controls, selected offerings, and planner widgets; onboarding-shell explanation belongs to home or onboarding, not planner.
- RULE: Render the main planner route with a weekly timetable grid spanning Monday through Sunday and only the vertical time range bounded by the earliest and latest selected class meetings.
- RULE: Prefer canonical subject titles from official or bulletin-derived sources over raw noisy public-schedule abbreviations whenever both are available.
- RULE: Favor layered gradients, monochrome noise, and floating accent objects over large flat surfaces.
- RULE: Prefer CSS-native or mathematically generated atmospheric backgrounds and pattern layers over raster decorative textures whenever browser support and runtime cost stay acceptable.
- RULE: Prefer container queries and CSS containment for reusable component adaptation before duplicating layout intent with breakpoint-only forks.
- RULE: Use `content-visibility`, `contain`, and `contain-intrinsic-size` selectively on heavy editorial or below-the-fold sections when they improve rendering cost without hiding critical interactive content.
- RULE: Treat `backdrop-filter` and translucent surfaces as progressive enhancement; ship contrast-safe opaque fallbacks first.
- RULE: Honor reduced-motion and stronger-contrast user preferences in the visual system rather than treating motion and translucency as unconditional decoration.
- RULE: Treat Apple atmosphere, Proton Authenticator web, and Perplexity Comet as inspiration only; never copy their assets, code, or distinctive strings.
- RULE: State clearly that no account is required.
- RULE: Keep the home surface editorial and non-technical, and keep any news cards traceable to official source URLs.
- RULE: Foreground current and near-term calendar and payment items before older published history.
- RULE: Keep search local to the site artifact and published data for the current slice.
- RULE: Keep local search broad enough to cover official graduate-program references, official double-degree references, and official secondary-study options that the product exposes.
- RULE: Keep inscriptions guidance highly traceable and link-driven; do not automate authenticated registration.
- RULE: Treat the final Connect to ChatGPT route and setup flow as a follow-up slice after planner state exists.
- RULE: Keep the main planner route focused on widgets and current schedule context; public-period and public-group selection controls belong in configuration.
